WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
Welcome to the Muse Cage Basketball Network.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:43.000
The Golden Democracy.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:50.000
84 assists on 135 field goals through 3 games.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:53.000
Every team wants to play team ball.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:57.000
But let's look at how Golden State does it.

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:01.000
What do you notice Draymond doing upon receiving the ball?

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:04.000
Is he looking to make a play for himself?

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:11.000
Or is he looking to make a play for someone else?

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:14.000
The way Golden State plays is rarer.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:18.000
The players go into attack mode when they are off the ball.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:20.000
Not on the ball.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:23.000
They don't force you to defend 1v1.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:32.000
They force you to defend 3v3.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
They force you to cover split actions, rip actions,

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:42.000
handoff actions, curl actions, slice actions, just to name a few.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:48.000
Playing this style takes advantage of the basic human challenge of communication.

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:53.000
Can you have the presence of mind to know who was setting the screen?

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:57.000
Have the presence of mind to know who was coming off the screen?

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:02.000
Have the presence of mind to communicate the proper strategy to your teammate involved in the screen?

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:09.000
And have the presence of mind to communicate crystal clearly while 20,000 fans scream at the top of their lungs?

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:13.000
And do it at split second.

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:18.000
This is what makes them so hard to contain for 48 minutes.

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:27.000
Having to be in constant communication defensively while dealing with the conditioning and physicality of the game wears teams down.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.000
It's hard to talk when you're out of breath, right?

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:39.000
Now imagine trying to communicate while at the same time being hit with screen after screen after screen after screen after screen after screen after screen.

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:46.000
Yes, they have great individual scores, but those scores are never stagnant.

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:52.000
They are constantly looking for each other, screening for each other, and passing to each other,

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
taking advantage of every defensive mistake.

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
These mistakes are built on lack of communication.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
Lack of communication creates division.

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:07.000
Division breaks teams apart.

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:10.000
A team apart can't play as one.

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:15.000
If you can't play as one, your season is done.

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:19.000
Long live the Golden Democracy.

